      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add monthly daily and stable release policy",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nOpenClaw cannot safely operate the new monthly daily/stable release model because release class, selector intent, protected policy authority, stable-line state, and publication evidence are not yet bound into one fail-closed contract.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis adds the `YYYY.M.PATCH` release classifier, strict selector policy, immutable policy/publish/postpublish evidence, authenticated exact-ref verification, stable-line lifecycle tooling, and class-aware closeout across the public release workflows. The release-candidate helper also emits the complete authenticated public macOS validation handoff and the runbook documents exact recovery steps. The authoritative `release/stable-lines.json` genesis is intentionally deferred to the July bootstrap PR, so strict stable publication remains blocked until that metadata exists and a fresh candidate preflight is run.\n\n## User Impact\n\nMaintainers can run daily releases with `latest` while preparing and patching a trailing-month stable line from `stable/YYYY.M.33`. Daily releases cannot accidentally advance the stable selector, and stable publication fails closed unless the exact protected policy, source branch, tag, workflow runs, and immutable artifacts agree.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- [x] Automated: focused stable-release unit and workflow-contract suite passes after rebasing onto current `origin/main`.\n- [x] Automated: workflow static checks, changed-file lint/format checks, YAML parsing, type checking, and `git diff --check` pass.\n- [x] Automated: inherited mainline CI repairs pass focused tooling, channel, model-fallback, fast-mode, outcome-contract, and plugin-SDK streaming suites plus core and extension source/test type checks, lint, and formatting; Linux-only resolver isolation is delegated to CI because macOS ships Bash 3.2.\n- [ ] Manual: exercise the July bootstrap stable preflight after authoritative stable-line metadata lands (deferred bootstrap release gate).\n- [ ] Manual: run all four cross-repository consumers with the real release integration token (BPT-05 release gate).\n\nNo authoritative stable-lines file is added by this PR.\n",
